==Abstract==

This IIP defines a hierarchical deterministic (HD) wallet structure for INTcoin using SHA3-256 (SHAKE256) based key derivation. This replaces the secp256k1-based BIP32 derivation which is incompatible with post-quantum signature schemes.

==Motivation==

BIP32 HD wallets rely on elliptic curve point multiplication for child key derivation, which is fundamentally incompatible with lattice-based signatures like ML-DSA-87. A new derivation scheme is needed that:

# Works with any signature algorithm (algorithm-agnostic)
# Maintains the hierarchical structure users expect
# Provides equivalent security properties to BIP32
# Supports hardened derivation for enhanced security

==Specification==

===Coin Type===

INTcoin uses coin type '''2210''' as registered in SLIP-0044.

===Derivation Path===

INTcoin follows the BIP44-style path structure:

<pre>
m / purpose' / coin_type' / account' / change / address_index
</pre>

Where:
* purpose = 44 (BIP44 compatible)
* coin_type = 2210 (INTcoin)
* account = account index (hardened)
* change = 0 for external (receiving), 1 for internal (change)
* address_index = sequential index

Example: <code>m/44'/2210'/0'/0/0</code> is the first receiving address of the first account.

===Master Key Generation===

From a BIP39 mnemonic seed:

<pre>
master_seed = PBKDF2(mnemonic, "mnemonic" + passphrase, 2048, 64, SHA512)
master_chain_code = SHAKE256(master_seed || 0x00, 32)
master_secret_key, master_public_key = ML-DSA-87.KeyGen(SHAKE256(master_seed || 0x01, 64))
</pre>

===Child Key Derivation===

For hardened derivation (index >= 0x80000000):

<pre>
data = 0x00 || parent_secret_key || index
intermediate = SHAKE256(parent_chain_code || data, 96)
child_chain_code = intermediate[0:32]
child_seed = intermediate[32:96]
child_secret_key, child_public_key = ML-DSA-87.KeyGen(child_seed)
</pre>

For non-hardened derivation (index < 0x80000000):

<pre>
data = parent_public_key || index
intermediate = SHAKE256(parent_chain_code || data, 96)
child_chain_code = intermediate[0:32]
child_seed = intermediate[32:96]
child_secret_key, child_public_key = ML-DSA-87.KeyGen(child_seed)
</pre>

'''Note''': Non-hardened derivation requires storing the child seed temporarily, as ML-DSA-87 key generation is not deterministic in the same way as ECDSA.

===Extended Key Serialization===

Extended keys use Bech32 encoding with human-readable prefixes:

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Type !! Prefix !! Approximate Length
|-
| Extended Public Key || ixpub || ~3600 characters
|-
| Extended Private Key || ixprv || ~10300 characters
|}

Format:
<pre>
version (4 bytes) || depth (1 byte) || parent_fingerprint (4 bytes) ||
child_index (4 bytes) || chain_code (32 bytes) || key_data
</pre>

Where key_data is:
* For ixpub: public_key (2592 bytes)
* For ixprv: 0x00 || secret_key (4896 bytes) || public_key (2592 bytes)

===Fingerprint Calculation===

<pre>
fingerprint = SHA3-256(public_key)[0:4]
</pre>

==Rationale==

===Why SHAKE256?===

SHAKE256 (a SHA3 extendable-output function) provides:
# Quantum resistance (256-bit security)
# Arbitrary output length without truncation concerns
# NIST standardization (FIPS 202)

===Why Store Both Keys?===

ML-DSA-87 cannot derive public keys from secret keys (unlike ECDSA). Extended private keys must contain both for practical usage.

===Large Key Sizes===

The extended key sizes (~10KB for private, ~3.6KB for public) are unavoidable given ML-DSA-87's key sizes. QR code encoding requires chunking or alternative transport mechanisms.

==Backwards Compatibility==

This specification is not compatible with BIP32/BIP44 wallets. INTcoin wallets must implement this IIP-44 specification.

Existing BIP39 mnemonics can be used, but will derive different keys than in Bitcoin wallets.

